HEADWORD: Enisled
<hw>En*isled"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>p. a.</pos> <def>Placed alone or
apart, as if on an island; severed, as an island.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧In the sea of life <xex>enisled</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>M. Arnold.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Enjail</ent>⟦br⟧
